    "The following sections provide an overview of key studies related to the respond function and highlight various cybersecurity solutions and AI use cases in each category.• Response planning-Response planning involves creating well-defined procedures to follow during and after an incident, aiming to limit its scope and impact.",
    "This includes developing a contingency plan that covers different attack scenarios and incorporating insights gained from ongoing incident response activities to update the plan.",
    "AI can automate response planning by establishing a dynamic case management tool that records, executes, and updates the contingency plan.• Automated responsibility allocation-Automated responsibility allocation serves as an intelligent decision support tool to assist security operation center (SOC) managers in assigning incident response duties based on the nature of the incident, staff expertise, and availability.",
    "While no specific research study within the review directly addresses this issue, Shah et al addressed resource allocation decisions in a cybersecurity operation center.",
    "They developed a stochastic, dynamic programming-based model that utilizes reinforcement learning to maintain optimal operational effectiveness in the face of disruptions caused by factors like alert generation rate, new alert patterns, and analyst absenteeism."
